ESDI strives to restore the traditional eco-social balance that is essential for the stability of the Horn of Africa. 


Our consultants possess keen knowledge of the natural and man-made forces that keep upsetting this crucial balance. They monitor the unique ways that these can align in any particular country at any given time, and devise workable interventions. 


As experts, they provide both conceptual and practical solutions to the chronic problems of the region: 

+ Environmental degradation; 
+ Political and social factionalism; 
+ Weak public institutions; 
+ Lack of food security, and 
+ Mass migration. 

ESDI is keen on sustainable development and provide policy framework that can assist our clients to achieve positive results.
